{"id":"chemical-electric-8","label":"Chemical Effects of Electric Current","lockAfter":2,"list":[{"id":"mcq","label":"Choose the correct answer","type":"mcq","commonData":{"title":"Multiple Choice Questions"},"data":[{"questions":[{"qText":"Which of the following is a bad conductor of electricity?","options":"Distilled water, Silver Nitrate, Sulphuric Acid, Copper Sulphate"},{"qText":"Which of the following does not conduct electricity?","options":"Sugar solution, Vinegar solution, Lemon juice solution, Caustic soda solution"},{"qText":"An electric current can produce ___.","options":"Heating effect, Chemical effect, Magnetic effect, * All of these "},{"qText":"Which of the following is a good conductor?","options":"Steel, Brick, Plastic, Cotton"},{"qText":"Electroplating is based on the ____ effect of electricity.","options":"chemical, heating, physical, magnetic"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"Waste from an electroplating factory must be disposed off","options":"according to the disposal guidelines of waste management bodies.\n              in the nearby river.\n              in the nearby pond.\n              in the agriculture field."},{"qText":"Flow of electron is called ____.","options":"electric current, electroplating, electrolyte, electrodes"},{"qText":"An electric lamp glows due to _____ effect.","options":"heating, magnetic, chemical, physical"},{"qText":"Electroplating prevents ____.","options":"corrosion, passing of current, dissociation, pollution"},{"qText":"Which of the following is not used for electroplating metal articles?","options":"Sodium, Nickel, Silver, Chromium"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"Iron objects can be protected by electroplating them with ____","options":"chromium, nickel, zinc, * all of these"},{"qText":"In LEDs, the longer lead (wire) is always connected to the _____ terminal.","options":"positive, negative, neutral, any terminal"},{"qText":"When electrodes are immersed in water and electricity passed, the bubbles formed on the positive terminal is ____.","options":" oxygen, hydrogen & oxygen, hydrogen, carbon dioxide"},{"qText":"When electrodes are immersed in water and electricity passed, the bubbles formed on the negative terminal is ____.","options":"hydrogen, carbon dioxide, oxygen, nitrogen"},{"qText":"We add little diluted sulphuric acid to copper sulphate solution during electroplating to ______.","options":"increase conductivity\n              burn copper sulphate\n              increase acidity\n              make the solution good conductor."}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"A coating of ____ is deposited on iron to protect it from corrosion and formation of rust.","options":"zinc, copper, silver, aluminium"},{"qText":"The process of depositing a layer of any desired metal on another material by means of electricity is called ____","options":"electroplating, electric plating, electric depositing, coating"},{"qText":"When electric current is passed through the copper sulphate solution, it dissociates into","options":"copper and sulphate, copper and sulphur, copper and oxygen"},{"qText":"The cans, used for storing food, are made by electroplating ____ on to irons.","options":"tin, chromium, zinc"},{"qText":"_____ is deposited on iron used in bridges and automobiles to protect it from corrosion and rust formation.","options":"zinc, chromium, tin, copper"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"Car parts, bath taps, kitchen gas burners, bicycle handlebars are electriplated with _____.","options":"chromium, tin, zinc, copper"},{"qText":"Which of the following is a good conductor?","options":"brass, leather, plastic, mica"},{"qText":"The process in which a chemical change takes place in a substance, when electric current is passed through is called ______.","options":"electrolysis, electrodes, thermal conduction"},{"qText":"The positive charged ions are called ___.","options":"cations, anions, positive ions"}]}]}]}